---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="FAQ - Free Prompt Studio" description="Frequently asked questions about Free Prompt Studio, the free browser-based AI prompt engineering toolkit.">
  <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

  <section class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">Is Free Prompt Studio really free?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">Yes. It is 100% free, open source, and runs entirely in your browser. No signup, no API keys, no hidden costs.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">Do you store my prompts?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">No. Everything stays in your browser. We do not collect, store, or transmit any data. The only local storage used is for your theme preference (light/dark mode).</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">What prompt frameworks are supported?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">We support CO-STAR, RISEN, CRAFT, and Freeform. Each framework has structured fields to help you build optimized prompts for any AI model.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">Which AI models are supported?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">The generator works with ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Llama, DeepSeek, and Mistral. The framework compilers adapt the output structure based on your selected model.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">How does the prompt analyzer work?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">It evaluates your prompt across 7 dimensions (clarity, role assignment, constraints, context, examples, tone, and output format) and gives a score from 0-100 with suggestions for improvement.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">Can I save or share my prompts?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">Yes. You can copy prompts to your clipboard, export them as .txt files, or share them via URL (the prompt data is encoded in the URL hash. No server is involved).</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">What is the response sanitizer?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">It cleans up AI-generated text by stripping backticks, removing common AI conversational fluff (~20 patterns), and collapsing excess whitespace. Useful when copying responses from ChatGPT or Claude.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">Does it work offline?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">Once the page is loaded, all functionality works without an internet connection (except for loading Google Fonts on first visit).</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">Is there a dark mode?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">Yes. Dark mode is the default. You can toggle it via the sun/moon icon in the header. Your preference is saved locally.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
